  "text": "Our study also demonstrated that reduced appetite was an independent predictor of short term mortality in cats. This finding is similar to human studies where reduced appetite has been linked to poor health outcomes in elderly patients [CITATION_1] . However, serum 25(OH)D concentrations remained a significant predictor of mortality when the results were corrected for reduced appetite. This suggests that the association between low serum vitamin D concentrations and mortality is not simply due to reduced dietary intake of vitamin D in hospitalised cats.",
